Hyper parameter selection for training

PDP analysis: * Best low QE and TE were approx 27 and 0.32 respectively.
* As pdp analysis is based on average results. low best QE and TE will be more or less than above predicted values.
1) Increase the dimension to reduce QE
2) Use guassian to reduce TE. also max itr and eps have impact on TE

  • Selected Hyper parameter for further training :

dimension: more than 10
Radius: guassian
distance: maximum, euclidean and minkowaski
initi proto: random
eps_0 : [0.1630,0.2311111]
scaling : both have similar graph

  • More range of Max iteration is checked max_itr :approx 98407 
h_dimension_T <- c(16)# 6
h_radius.type_T <- c("letremy")
h_dist.type_T <- c("letremy") # eucli
h_maxit_T <-c(98407)#4000
h_eps_0_T <- c(0.2311111) #0.2311111
h_init.proto_T <- c("obs")
h_scaling_T <- c("unitvar") # center

Clustering

  • AIC, BIC check were performed on the above SOM brero model.

  • Detailed analysis is noted in Best_K_evaluation.rmd

  • Two different method used for this analysis.

  • Min AIC and BIC was found at k <-c(3,4,8,9)

  • Sillhouette and Dunn index were checked for above four K sizes.

  • Average silhouette for all four K values was 0.19,0.18,0.2 and 0.2

  • Dunn Index was in 0.12,0.12,0.16 and 0.16. Slight difference was after third decimals

  • Cluster K =9 has the largest Dunn index= 0.1665

  • AIC selects more complex models in comparision with BIC. Such complex models have better predictive accuracy. [Reference :Machine Learning A Probabilistic Perspective ]
